                                <h1><strong>IEEE PUNE BLOCKCHAIN GROUP</strong></h1>
    <p style="font-size: medium;">Applications for blockchain technology are fascinating and span financial, supply-chain, Internet of Things, and enterprise domains. Blockchain is a publicly verifiable, shared, and unchangeable ledger that records the history of transactions. Each block in the ledger consists of a set of transactions, a timestamp, a digest of the block before it, and other information. Blockchain technology has demonstrated enormous promise recently in financial applications such as Litecoin, Bitcoin, smart contracts, etc. As a result, numerous industry consortia have worked together to identify an appropriate platform for transactions enabled by blockchain technology. Blockchain technology and cryptographic primitives are predicted to change the way that e-governance, healthcare, and Internet of Things applications are used in the near future in terms of security, privacy, efficiency, transparency, and fault-resistance.</p>
    
    
    
    
